Seven people perished in a horror crash in the KwaZulu-Natal Midlands on Saturday morning. KwaZulu-Natal Emergency Medical Services spokesman Robert McKenzie said the accident, between a bakkie and a car, took place on the R617 near Appelsbosch. "Tragically seven people have sustained fatal injuries and one person has been treated for critical injuries. "The exact cause of the crash involving a bakkie and a car is not known at this stage. Police are investigating."